      "date": "2017-01-11 16:23:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI guess I'm ok with removing the \"error:\" prefix of the message is clear. \n\nI'm not sure where \"--list-commands\" is implemented? I couldn't find it anywhere except the error message. It would also need to be added to the man page for both lfs and lctl and any other tools that are using the same command parser.",
