          "date": "2017-01-05 19:07:22.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-5170 lfs: Standardize error messages in lfs utility",
        "message": "LU-5170 lfs: Standardize error messages in lfs utility\n\nThis patch makes usability improvements to the error messages\ndisplayed by the lfs utility when the user provides invalid\narguments.  Messages are now prefixed with the name of the utility\nto improve readability when run from scripts.  Message text is now\nconsistent when the same error type occurs.  String values provided\nby the user are now delimited by single quotes to separate them\nfrom the rest of the message text.\n\nSubsequent patches will provide additional improvments, such as the\n'--list-commands' option.\n\nSigned-off-by: Steve Guminski <stephenx.guminski@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2129dc7d301352a161119f80f81da507c2fc82df\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
